-- Microsoft interested in search pact with Yahoo, not acquisition
-- 
-- Wed Nov 19, 2008 12:06pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/11/19/us-microsoft-idUSTRE4AI5JW20081119

 

 (Reuters) - Microsoft Corp CEO Steve Ballmer on Wednesday said the company is "not immune" to "current economic realities". Highlights: 

 * Microsoft's Ballmer says company looking at every aspect of business for opportunities to reduce costs, "utilize resources more efficiently" * Microsoft's Ballmer says expects "much slower growth" in headcount for the remainder of this financial year and possibly next year * Microsoft's Ballmer: "we are done with all acquisitions discussions with Yahoo" * Microsoft's Ballmer says would still be interested in search collaboration with Yahoo * Microsoft's Ballmer says would be "very open" to Yahoo search talks, but there are "no active discussion on that front"